                  <p class="ia-table-text">The main benefit monetised in this IA is the improvement to consumer experience due to a reduction in outages. Legislation will allow Ofgem to introduce guaranteed standards of performance, and this can include requiring heat network operators to pay compensation to customers for periods of heat outages. This possibly moves some of the cost from consumers to operators which in turn incentivises operators to reduce the frequency and duration of outages. Though this legislation allows the introduction of guaranteed standards of performance by the regulator, it does not introduce this directly. The impacts of these standards, however, are a likely result of the legislation and have therefore been captured in the analysis.</p>
                  <p class="ia-table-text">There are additional benefits from this policy which have not been quantified due to a lack of appropriate metrics. Compared to the previous consultation IA, the scope of this IA has reduced to reflect the scope of the Heat Networks (Market Framework) (Great Britain) Regulations 2025 and therefore it is not suitable to include these previously quantified benefits in this current IA. </p>
