            <p><b>Results </b></p>
            <p>The analysis suggests that set-up costs are expected to be £9.1m (undiscounted) in the first year. Of this, £7.6m are Ofgem set-up costs and £1.5m are consumer advocacy body costs. Figure 2 shows the annual operating costs of heat network regulation by the quadripartite regime, where the average would be between £24m and £30m, with a central estimate of £27m (all undiscounted). For the central estimate, Ofgem costs make up £21m of the average annual estimate (undiscounted). The sensitivity scenarios used are low growth with low cost assumptions, central growth with central cost assumptions, and high growth with high cost assumptions. </p>
            <p><b>Figure 2 – quadripartite cost over a 30-year appraisal period </b></p>
